%N A368212 Square spiral of positive integers built by greedy algorithm such that each value corresponds to the area of the connected component with terms of the same value and containing this value.
%C A368212 In other words, we tile the plane with polyominoes as small as possible, and for any k > 0, two k-ominoes cannot share an edge.
%C A368212 This sequence is a variant of A368148.
%C A368212 Empirically, the spiral has 4-fold rotational symmetry.
